1 (2) Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, an
2 electronic voting system acquired on or after January 1, 2026, and
3 approved by the board of state canvassers under section 795a, must
4 not include any parts or equipment produced or provided by an
5 entity that has any covered communications equipment or service
6 listed on the Federal Communications Commission's website as
7 required under 47 USC 1601. The approval of an electronic voting
8 system by the board of state canvassers under section 795a is not
9 negated if the entity that has any covered communications equipment
10 or service listed on the Federal Communications Commission's
11 website is added to the Federal Communications Commission's website
12 after the electronic voting system was approved by the board of
13 state canvassers under section 795a. As used in this subsection,
14 "covered communications equipment or service" means that term as
15 defined in 47 USC 1608.
16 (3) (2) Electronic tabulating equipment that counts votes at
17 the precinct before the close of the polls must provide a method
18 for rendering the equipment inoperable if vote totals are revealed
19 before the close of the polls. Electronic tabulating equipment that
20 tabulates ballots, including absentee ballots, at a central
21 location must be programmed to reject a ballot if the choices
22 recorded on an elector's ballot for an office or a question exceed
23 the number that the elector is entitled to vote for on that office
24 or question, if no valid choices are recorded on an elector's
25 ballot, or if, in a primary election, votes are recorded for
26 candidates of more than 1 political party.
27 (4) (3) Each jurisdiction in this state conducting an election
28 shall equip each polling place with at least 1 accessible voting
29 device as required under subsection (1)(n).
