1 (9) If the board of state canvassers determines that an
2 electronic voting system that was approved under subsection (1) no
3 longer meets the requirements described in that subsection, the
4 board of state canvassers may disapprove that electronic voting
5 system. An Subject to subsection (10), an electronic voting system
6 that has been disapproved by the board of state canvassers under
7 this subsection shall must not be used in an election, unless it
8 that electronic voting system is reapproved by the board of state
9 canvassers under subsection (1).
10 (10) For an electronic voting system acquired on or after
11 January 1, 2026, the board of state canvassers shall not approve
12 that electronic voting system if that electronic voting system
13 includes any parts or equipment produced or provided by an entity
14 that has any covered communications equipment or service listed on
15 the Federal Communications Commission's website as required under
16 47 USC 1601. This subsection does not prohibit the approval of an
17 improvement or change to an approved electronic voting system under
18 subsection (6) or the repair, maintenance, or acquisition of
19 components necessary for the proper operation of an electronic
20 voting system that was acquired and approved before January 1,
21 2026. As used in this subsection, "covered communications equipment
22 or service" means that term as defined in 47 USC 1608.
